This paper discusses the evaluation of academic journals in the field of business and management, which involves the use of various citation indicators and ranking methods. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cryptography and security (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper's focus on citation analysis and ranking methods suggests that cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CR and cs.AI, while cs.SI is less likely but still relevant due to the paper's discussion of field effects.
